publicationXreff52.standardName: Identification of metabolic pathways in Daphnia magna explaining hormetic effects of selective serotonin reuptake inhibitors and 4-nonylphenol using transcriptomic and phenotypic responses.

pathway.author: [Egonw, Mkutmon]

comments.content: Various biological pathways affected in response to exposure to serotonin reuptake inhibitors. After exposure the genes lace, cDASE, GlcT-1, ldh, Acon, Ddc, Fbp, and thiolase are upregulated, while Pfk, UGP, and ATPC are downregulated.
